{
  "texts": [
    "Thus, GENRE [18], based on the title as DocID and leveraging the generative model BART [138] and pre-built DocID prefix, achieved superior retrieval performance across 11 datasets in KILT.",
    "Following GENRE, GERE [27], CorpusBrain [28], Re3val [257], and CorpusBrain++ [80] also based their work on title DocIDs for Wikipedia-based tasks.",
    "Notably, LLM-URL [376] directly generated URLs using ChatGPT prompts, achieving commendable performance after removing invalid URLs.",
    "However, in the web search scenario [205], document titles in the corpus often have significant duplication and many meaningless titles, making it unfeasible to use titles alone as DocIDs.",
    "Thus, Ultron [371] effectively addressed this issue by combining URLs and titles as DocIDs, identifying documents through keywords in web page URLs and titles.Sub-strings of Documents."
  ]
}